Slow Cooker Creamed Corn
  --Chungah Rhee

3x15.25 oz cans whole kernel corn, drained
1 c milk
1 tbsp sugar
1/4 tsp pepper
8 oz cream cheese, cubed
1/2 c (1 stick) unsalted butter, cut into thin slices

Place corn in slow cooker. Stir in milk, sugar, and pepper until well combined. Without stirring, top with butter and cream cheese. Cover and cook on high heat for 2-3 hrs. Uncover and stir until butter and cream cheese are well combined. Cover and cook on high for an additional 15 min. Serve immediately.
